FivePoints.GraphNavigation

Class MapObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • FivePoints.GraphNavigation.MapObject

  • public class MapObject
extends java.lang.Object
    MapObject is a wrapper-ish class for maintaining an object with definite length and a category defined by World.Node. Used internally by the controller.

                 int x2,
                 int y1,
                 int y2)
        Construct a new MapObject given the specified coordinate points.
        Parameters:
        type - The type (World.Node) of MapObject to be created.
        x1 - The x coordinate for the bottom left point.
        x2 - The x coordinate for the bottom right point.
        y1 - The y coordinate for the top left point.
        y2 - The y coordinate for the top right point.
